# Neurodivergent Life Skills & Career Development\
\
## Overview\
\
The DreamZilla curriculum is a comprehensive 6-week program designed to support neurodivergent young adults (ages 18-24) in developing life skills, exploring career paths, and building AI literacy. This curriculum is integrated into the Dyslexic AI platform as part of the Cognitive Partner system.\
\
### Program Philosophy\
\
- **Neurodivergent-Affirming**: Celebrates neurodivergent strengths and honors diverse ways of thinking\
- **Trauma-Informed**: Prioritizes safety, choice, and empowerment\
- **Brain-Based**: Works with, not against, individual cognitive patterns\
- **Voice-First**: Supports multiple modes of interaction\
- **Peer-Coach Style**: Warm, collaborative, and non-judgmental\
\
---\
\
## Program Structure\
\
### Five Key Concentration Areas\
\
1. **Self-Awareness & Cognitive Discovery**\
   - Understanding personal brain patterns\
   - Identifying strengths and challenges\
   - Building self-knowledge foundation\
\
2. **Executive Function & System Design**\
   - Mapping task breakdowns\
   - Creating personalized support systems\
   - Experimenting with strategies\
\
3. **Energy Management & Boundaries**\
   - Tracking energy patterns\
   - Identifying energy leaks\
   - Setting protective boundaries\
\
4. **Communication & Self-Advocacy**\
   - Developing advocacy language\
   - Practicing self-advocacy scenarios\
   - Building communication confidence\
\
5. **Career Development & AI Literacy**\
   - Exploring career paths aligned with brain profiles\
   - Understanding AI disruption and opportunities\
   - Building AI literacy skills\
\
